  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nCurrently, running `forge build --deny-warnings` or `forge test --deny-warnings` applies the `--deny-warnings` file to all the files compiled.\r\n\r\nIt can happen that a library you use emits a warning, which makes the whole build fail.\r\n\r\nIdeally, the user could decide to enable / disable `--deny-warnings` to specific folders (for example, apply `--deny-warnings` to everything in `src/` but not in `lib/`).\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
